option.value: - added test for line numbers in stack traces

task.summary: fixed bug when trying to leak private variables while using "module.exports = ..."
added support for older node versions
- changed API - introduced __set__ and __get__ to rewired modules
namespaced all variables within the __set__ method so you can really set all variables
added backwards compatibility to node version
removed "use strict"; to avoid influencing not-strict modules
fixed bug when node_modules folder is missing
- changed browserify version to 1.13.5 - fixed global var injection in the browser
- fixed bug when using b.addEntry() - small fixes
- fixed parsing error when trying to set a function as mock - update to mocha 1.3.x - fixed minor IE issues
- Introduced webpack bundler for rewire (work in progress, some tests are not running)
- Woops! Adjusted test to API change :)
- Fixed crash when a global module has been used in the browser
- Fixed error with client-side bundlers when a module was ending with a comment
- Improved client-side rewire() with webpack - Fixed webpack-version in "devDependencies"

- added Coffee-Script support closes #8 (jashkenas/coffee-script#2707) - renamed internalRewire.js to simply rewire.js - moved all the stuff related to manipulating the module environment to moduleEnv.js
- added Coffee-Script to devDependencies (fixes Travis crash)
- current state after merging branches from webpack/rewire
- version bump to 1.1.0 - updated README and package.json - removed Makefile: Use npm test instead - added node 0.9 to travis
- added test for line numbers in stack traces
- added a test for the case where a comment is on the last line
- Added deprecation warning for client-side bundlers - Updated package.json for node v0.10 - Removed tests for client-side bundlers - Updated .travis.yml for node v0.10 - Updated README
- Forced fake package.json to be committed
